    • Method Detail

      • removeAll

        ConcurrentStack<E> removeAll()
        Atomically drains the stack and returns its contents in a new instance. This can be interpreted as a "clone" then "clear" operation, in one.
        Returns:
        a new stack that has all of the contents that were held by this stack, in the same order

      • drainTo

        void drainTo(Collection<? super E> coll)
        Atomically drains the stack by popping all elements from the stack and adding them to the given collection. The top of the stack will be the first item added to the collection.

        If the given collection is thread-safe and published to multiple threads, the additions of elements may not appear atomic.

        Parameters:
        coll - the collection into which items are drained
